THE BATTLE OF NORTH CAPE AND THE 1ST ST MARGARETS CUBS
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    
    The Battle of North Cape began Christmas Day 1943 when the German
    battlecruiser Scharnhorst and five escorting destroyers left their
    base in Altenfjord to intercept two Arctic Convoys rounding
    Norway's North Cape. Convoy JW55B was transporting essential
    supplies to the Soviet Union, and RA 55A was returning to the U.K.

