BEE NICE TO THE BUMBLEBEE THIS SUMMER
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    
    Richmond Council is encouraging residents not to attack any nests.
    Normally bumblebee nests live for around 2-3 months, they do not
    cause any structural damage and they do not swarm. They are also
    not aggressive insects and are generally only interested in finding
    flowers. The only time when they may act defensively is if
    something disturbs their nest.

